content: Hey Benjamin, I’m working on my website’s SEO. Any tips for a beginner?
I usually use tools like Google Keyword Planner or SEMrush. Look for keywords with good search volume but not too competitive. Long-tail ones are easier to rank for. What's your site about?
It’s my portfolio for UI/UX design. Hoping to get some freelance work from it.
Nice! Try keywords like "freelance UI/UX designer" or "UI design portfolio." You could also write a blog or case studies to boost SEO.
I’ve been thinking about blogging but not sure what to write. Any ideas?
You could write about your design process, tips, or break down your projects. It’ll show off your skills and help with SEO.
A little, but I’m not sure about the right keywords. How do you find them?
Hey! Sure thing. Start with your on-page SEO—title tags, meta descriptions, and keywords. Have you worked on those yet?
No problem at all! Happy to help. Good luck with your site!
That’s awesome advice. Thanks, Benjamin! Mind if I hit you up again if I need more help?
Hey Liam! How’s it going? Must be fun working with indie artists!
Hey Safi, it’s awesome! Lots of creativity. Every project’s different. What are you working on?
I’m on a new web project. Building a clean UI for a startup. I’m always tweaking stuff though. Do you ever feel like your work’s never done?
